  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Double-blind randomized controlled trial to investigate the impact of two human milk
      fortifiers on acid-base status and longitudinal growth and weight gain in preterm infants.

      Two different compositions are tested, main difference is in electrolyte composiiton.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Two groups each consisting of 15 infants with a birth weight below 2000g are
      studied.randomization is startified by three birth weigth classes (&lt;1000g, 1000-1500g,1500 -
      2000g) human milk fortifier is introduced in two steps after oral feeding is achieved. two
      acid-base status and electrolyte concentrations are measured. when metabolic acidosis,
      defined as BE &lt; -6 mmol/l, occurs fortifier feeding is stopped, and after a wash-out period
      of three days the alternative product is used.again, occurence of metabolic acidosis, need
      for oral bicarbonate and effect on longitudinal growth an weight gain are registered.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
